  "prompt": "What is the function of centrosomes in plant cells?",
  "response": "Centrosomes are typically not found in plant cells. Instead, plant cells have structures called microtubule-organizing centers (MTOCs) that perform similar functions to centrosomes in animal cells. The main MTOC in plant cells is located in the nuclear envelope and helps to organize the spindle apparatus during cell division. Additionally, plant cells have smaller MTOCs distributed throughout the cell, which help to maintain the cell's shape and facilitate intracellular transport.",
